There are many ways to propagate discrimination, but some common tactics include:

1. portraying members of a particular group as inferior, dangerous, or untrustworthy;

2. using stereotypes or caricatures to depict members of a group as less than human;

3. spreading rumors or falsehoods about members of a group;

4. encouraging physical or verbal abuse of members of a group;

5. segregating or isolating members of a group;

6. denying members of a group equal access to education, employment, housing, or other opportunities;

7. denying or limiting members of a group the right to vote, hold office, or participate in other aspects of civic life.
